# React Development Guidelines

## Version and Compiler

This project uses:

- **React 19**: Latest version with automatic optimizations and improved performance
- **React Compiler**: (Previously React Forget) Automatic fine-grained updates and optimizations
- **TanStack Start**: Full integration with React 19 and React Compiler

These tools together provide:

- Automatic dependency tracking
- Optimized re-renders
- Automatic memoization
- Fine-grained updates
- Better performance by default

This means we can write simpler, more maintainable code without manual optimizations. The compiler will handle most performance optimizations automatically.

## Overview

These guidelines establish comprehensive best practices for React development in our TanStack Start application, covering components, hooks, performance, and general best practices. These guidelines are optimized for React 19 with React Compiler.

